name: Hayling Billy train ticket cushion
description:
Commemorating the 50th Anniversary of the closure of the Hayling Billy line.

Designed from a real Hayling Billy ticket, bought on and featuring the date of the train's last day of activity; 2nd November 1963.

Measuring approx 50cm by 24cm, and made in the UK.
100% Cotton zipped washable cover, with a polyester cushion filler.

If you are local to Hayling Island and would like to collect your cushion in person, please email me: hello@ashley-allen.co.uk

name:
SALE! Windsor Castle
Train Ticket Tote Bag
description: WAS £15, now £7! Limited Edition cotton Tote Bag, with a royal themed train ticket design; 'from Windsor and Eton Central to Windsor Castle', dated the 6th February 1952. For a unique and playful British souvenir of 2012 and '13, this is just the ticket! Part of my Limited Edition collection to celebrate 'the Best of British'. The collection includes cushions, tote bags, tea towels and bone china cups - all made in the UK with the regal purple design, distinctly British royal destinations, and the date of our Queen's Diamond Jubilee. Other destinations include: Buckingham Palace. Ideal for those who love a bit of British iconography, or enjoy homewares and accessories with an eclectic twist! Dimensions: Approx 38cm wide, 37cm tall. Gusset approx 12cm deep. Handles approx 33cm long. Made in the UK, and 100% cotton. Wash at max 30 degrees. Can be gift wrapped in quality kraft paper and finished with a purple grosgrain ribbon upon request. For your information ticket details are representational and may not reflect actual ticket details. Produced under licence from ATOC an TfL.
